data.title: Live From... the Hook (2006)
data.meta_description: Live From... the Hook: Directed by Joseph W. Grafmuller. This is a homegrown film capturing the rich history and collaborative spirit of the Charlottesville music scene. The film focuses on local rock legends Bob Girard of Johnny Sportcoat and Charlie Pastorfield of Skip Castro Band, with appearances by many other musicians, ranging from members of Skip Castro, the Casuals, the Charlottesville Blues All Stars and Indecision all the way to the Hackensaw Boys, American Dumpster and The Dave Matthews Band.
